  * "RSS Δ 1 heap" is the headline judge. BEFORE the RAD-1 lazy-`next_free`
    fix it INCLUDES the ~16 MiB registry `next_free` first-touch (4096 slots ×
    ~7488 B stride under `production` = 4096 distinct pages). AFTER the fix it
    collapses to the primordial-segment cost only (~0.1 MiB). Measured on this
    host: 16.11 MiB → 0.11 MiB; first-alloc latency 8.6 ms → 0.17 ms.

